  "texts": [
    "In essence, the final essay score in the Siamese Bi-LSTM architecture takes into account the essay's semantic features, coherence, and the underlying rating criteria information within the essays.",
    "In another note, Wang et al. (2018) proposed a reinforcement learning approach that utilizes quadratic weighted kappa as guidance to optimize the essay scoring system, capturing rating information.",
    "Uto and Okano (2020) investigated the performance of AES methods in accordance with the characteristics of raters inscribed implicitly in the ratings.",
    "To build a robust neural network AES methods, they proposed a two-stage architecture that uses Item Response Theory (IRT) model alongside the convolutional recurrent neural networks.",
    "The IRT model is used to model the relationship between the raters and the essays and handle the possible bias that can be introduced in the scores."
